to\": 172}, {\"ngram\": \"the historic Olympic Airways aircraft\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 213}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Mount Olympus\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 229}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 253}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 257, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sourmena Stadium\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legendary Boeing 727, which had been abandoned at Elliniko Airport since its last flight in 2001, was originally purchased in 1968 by Aristotle Onassis for the Olympic Airways fleet.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 322, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_727\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boeing 727\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_727\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_727\"}, {\"begin\": 446, \"end\": 463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aristotle Onassis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\"}, {\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6358697596636742e-37, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Elliniko Airport\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 378}, {\"ngram\": \"its last flight\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More recently, Andreas Christodoulides, President of the Cypriot company Zela Aviation, bought the historic aircraft, which, after refurbishing and renovating it, he donated to the Municipality of Elliniko.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases